## Responsible Disclosure Policy

This security research was conducted in accordance with industry-standard
responsible disclosure practices:

### Disclosure Timeline

- **Initial Disclosure:** May 22, 2026
- **Vendor Acknowledgment:** May 23, 2026 (Dr. Chopper, developer@sarvam.ai)
- **Vendor Promise:** Follow-up after internal investigation
- **Disclosure Window:** 32 days
- **Window Expiration:** June 23, 2026
- **Publication Date:** June 23, 2026

### Vendor Notification

Sarvam AI was notified on May 22, 2026 that:

1. A comprehensive vulnerability report had been prepared
2. Public disclosure would occur after 32 days if no response was received
3. The researchers were available for technical discussion during the disclosure window
4. Coordination on public disclosure timing was welcomed

### Vendor Response

On May 23, 2026, Dr. Chopper from Sarvam AI (developer@sarvam.ai) responded:

> Thanks for the detailed debug suite — really appreciate the depth. I've shared
> the ZIP, the investigation report, and the raw logs with the API and Models team.
> They'll dig into the tools/streaming pathway and the 30B variant as you've
> recommended.
> 
> We'll come back to you here once the team has more.

No follow-up was received despite this explicit promise.

### Compliance

This publication complies with:

- Industry-standard disclosure windows
- Good-faith effort requirements for vendor contact
- Adequate time for remediation before public disclosure
- Technical accuracy and evidence-based reporting

### Contact

For questions about this disclosure:
- **Email:** flawme@proton.me
- **Report ID:** SARVAM-2026-001

---

## Disclaimer

This security research is provided for educational and responsible disclosure
purposes only. The findings described in this report are based on black-box
testing of a publicly accessible API. The researchers make no claims about
the internal architecture, training methodology, or implementation details
of the assessed product. All observations are based solely on observable
input/output behavior.

The researchers followed responsible disclosure practices and provided the
vendor with adequate time (32 days) to respond and remediate before public
disclosure. The vendor acknowledged receipt and promised follow-up but never
delivered. This publication is made in good faith after the disclosure
window elapsed without vendor follow-up.
